The paper discusses privacy challenges associated with potential loss, theft, or misuse of genomic data, and proposes efficient techniques based on private set operations to address genomic privacy. This suggests that the paper belongs to the category of computer security (cs.CR). The paper also involves data management and analysis, which could fall under the categories of databases (cs.DB) and cybernetics (cs.CY). Additionally, the paper discusses personalized medicine, which could be related to machine learning (cs.LG) and information retrieval (cs.IR).
